<Window x:Class="PersonalFinanceTracker.MainWindow"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
        xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
        xmlns:local="clr-namespace:PersonalFinanceTracker"
        xmlns:viewModels="clr-namespace:PersonalFinanceTracker.ViewModels"
        mc:Ignorable="d"
        Title="MainWindow" Height="450" Width="800">
    <Window.DataContext>
        <viewModels:MainViewModel/>
    </Window.DataContext>
    <Grid>
        <ListView ItemsSource="{Binding Transactions}">
            <ListView.View>
                <GridView>
                    <GridViewColumn Header="Description" DisplayMemberBinding="{Binding Description}" Width="200"></GridViewColumn>
                    <GridViewColumn Header="Amount" DisplayMemberBinding="{Binding Amount}" Width="100"></GridViewColumn>
                    <GridViewColumn Header="Category" DisplayMemberBinding="{Binding Category}" Width="200"></GridViewColumn>
                    <GridViewColumn Header="Date" DisplayMemberBinding="{Binding Date}" Width="200"></GridViewColumn>
                </GridView>
            </ListView.View>
        </ListView>
    </Grid>
</Window>


<!-- 
** Simple and Scalable Project: Personal Finance Tracker **

Project Overview

A Personal Finance Tracker application is a great project to start with WPF. 
It involves creating a desktop application that allows users to track their income, expenses, and savings. 
The application can be expanded with features like reporting, data visualization, and budget planning.

Project Features

*** Basic Features ***

User Authentication (Login/Signup)
Adding Income and Expense Entries
Viewing Transaction History
Categorizing Transactions (e.g., Food, Transport, Entertainment)
Balance Summary (Total Income, Total Expenses, Net Balance)

*** Intermediate Features ***

Data Visualization (Charts and Graphs)
Budget Planning
Exporting Data (CSV, PDF)
Notifications and Reminders

*** Advanced Features ***

Multi-user Support
Cloud Syncing
AI-driven Expense Analysis
Mobile App Integration
-->